  "steps": [
    {
      "type": "content",
      "content": {
        "title": {
          "english": "Asking: What is this? (Masculine)"
        },
        "text": "To ask about a single masculine object near you in Moroccan Darija, you use the phrase \"شنو هادا؟\". This literally translates to \"What is this (masculine)?\".",
        "examples": [
          {
            "arabic": "شنو هادا؟",
            "english": "What is this? (masculine)",
            "transliteration": "Shnu hada?"
          },
          {
            "arabic": "هادا قلم.",
            "english": "This is a pen.",
            "transliteration": "Hada qalam."
          }
        ],
        "audioText": "Shnu hada?"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "content",
      "content": {
        "title": {
          "english": "Answering: This is... (Masculine)"
        },
        "text": "When someone asks \"شنو هادا؟\" about a masculine object, you can answer by simply saying \"هادا...\" followed by the object's name. \"هادا\" means \"this is\" (for masculine).",
        "examples": [
          {
            "arabic": "هادا كتاب.",
            "english": "This is a book.",
            "transliteration": "Hada ktab."
          },
          {
            "arabic": "هادا ستيلو.",
            "english": "This is a pen.",
            "transliteration": "Hada stilo."
          }
        ],
        "audioText": "Hada ktab."
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "content",
      "content": {
        "title": {
          "english": "Asking: What is this? (Feminine)"
        },
        "text": "Similar to masculine objects, for a single feminine object near you, the question changes slightly. You say \"شنو هادي؟\" where \"هادي\" indicates a feminine noun. It means \"What is this (feminine)?\".",
        "examples": [
          {
            "arabic": "شنو هادي؟",
            "english": "What is this? (feminine)",
            "transliteration": "Shnu hadi?"
          },
          {
            "arabic": "هادي محفظة.",
            "english": "This is a bag.",
            "transliteration": "Hadi maḥfaḍa."
          }
        ],
        "audioText": "Shnu hadi?"
      }
    },
